2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 86
BY SENATOR MCMATH
SENATE. Prohibits wearing eyeglasses with audio video capabilities in the Senate chamber
unless approved by Senate President.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To amend and readopt Senate Rule No. 1.2 of the Rules of Order of the Senate to prohibit
3 wearing any eyeglasses with video or audio recording capability in the Senate
4 chamber without approval from the President of the Senate.
5 BE IT RESOLVED by the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana to amend and
6 readopt Senate Rule 1.2 of the Rules of Order of the Senate to read as follows:
7 Rule 1.2 Senate Chamber
8 A. The Senate Chamber shall not be used as a public meeting place. It shall
9 be used only by the legislature, the Democratic State Central Committee, and the Republican
10 State Central Committee, except that when the legislature is not in session, the Pelican Boys
11 State; the Pelican Girls State; the Jaycee Action, Silver Haired, Camp Fire Councils Youth,
12 and YMCA Youth legislatures; the Young Democrats of Louisiana; and the College
13 Republicans shall be allowed to use the chamber. The Secretary or his designee shall be
14 present at each such meeting and shall supervise and control the use of the chamber and any
15 of its facilities. Any such group desiring to use the chamber shall contact the Secretary at
16 least thirty days prior to the date on which the meeting is scheduled.
17 B. No meeting or public hearing of any legislative committee shall be held
