1 in the Senate Chamber at any time.
2 C. The President shall designate a place in the Senate Chamber for the news
3 media, and the members thereof shall have free access thereto. Accreditation of members
4 of any news media for admission shall be administered by the President.
5 D. The Senate Library and Sections C and D shall be for the exclusive use of
6 members of the legislature and the persons designated in Senate Rule 1.3. No registered
7 lobbyist shall be permitted in the Senate Library. Section B shall be for the exclusive use of
8 the senators and immediate members of their family. No other person shall be allowed to sit
9 in this Section.
10 E. No disruptive conversations shall be held in the Senate Chamber. No
11 conversation shall be held within the chamber, except in the presence of a senator, nor shall
12 any conversation be held across the rail.
13 F. Seating facilities shall be provided for the public in the Senate Gallery.
14 Admittance shall be under such conditions as are determined by the President.
15 G. A former member of the senate, except one who is a registered lobbyist,
16 may enter those portions of the Senate Floor designated as Sections B, C, and D, the Senate
17 Library, the office of the secretary, and that portion of the floor behind the Secretary's desk.
18 H. No person shall wear eyeglasses that have video or audio recording
19 capabilities inside the Senate Chamber without the express permission of the President
20 of the Senate.
